cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper deals with fine-grained visual classification, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a training method for attention networks, which involves learning an inverse mapping function, indicating that machine learning (cs.LG and cs.AI) is also relevant. The paper also mentions the use of attention models for localizing and attending to discriminative object parts, which falls under multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper mentions the use of orthogonal initialization of attention weights, which is a technique used in neural networks (cs.NE).
